The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, June 04, 2004 				 Storm toll
																								June 3: Four people were struck down by lightning in Burdwan and Metro services in Calcutta were stalled during the storm and rain tonight. 																								Rabya Khatoon, 12, was killed and nine girls were injured when lightning struck at Ichubhagra Bazar Madarsa Secondary School. Three others died elsewhere in the district																								Officials of the underground railway said trains were stopped from 7:30 to 8:30 after a tree fell on the tracks outside the tunnel near Tollygunge. Trains from Sealdah and Howrah were stopped for half-an-hour.
